The article discusses an executive order issued by President Barack Obama to advance the goals of the Power Africa initiative, which aims to expand access to electricity in Sub-Saharan Africa. The order establishes the President's Power Africa Working Group, which will coordinate efforts among various government agencies and stakeholders to achieve the initiative's objectives. The order also emphasizes the importance of partnering with African governments, the private sector, and civil society to increase electricity generation and access in both urban and rural areas. The Power Africa initiative aims to add 30,000 megawatts of capacity and 60 million new connections by 2030, while promoting cleaner energy sources and inclusive economic growth in Sub-Saharan Africa.